properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued February 2 at 1:32AM PST until February 3 at 7:00PM PST by NWS Elko NV
properties.description:
* WHAT...Post cold front northwest to north winds of 30 to 40
mph with gusts of 50 to 60 mph likely. Gusts up to 70 mph
possible especially in higher elevations and in areas where
the terrain channels the wind.

* WHERE...Northwestern Nye County.

* WHEN...From late Sunday night through Monday evening.

* IMPACTS...High winds may move loose debris, damage property
and cause power outages. Travel could be difficult especially
for high profile vehicles.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM LATE TONIGHT THROUGH MONDAY EVENING
